               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="177110230065"></xptr>Q. Did you see the prisoner cut out the marks?</p>
               <p>Coates. No; I had a piece and was going to put it into the water, by his order; but the Captain was coming on shore, and then he bid me put it into the barge; he called for the cook's axe to chop it into the boat; I did not see what he did; I was in the ship.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you see the mark on that piece?</p>
               <p>Coates. I cannot say, Captain Hill was on board, and was gone down into the cabin.</p>
               <p>Q. How many of the pieces might there be in the barge where he chopt?</p>
               <p>Coates. There might be thirty or forty pieces, we put some out afterwards, some into the water, and other vessels for the mate.</p>
