            . I was in this trade about the time this voyage was undertaken. The common wages of a chief mate at that time on board such ships was not less than four pounds, sometimes four pounds five shillings.</p>
               <p>Captain Hill. I did not hire the prisoner, nor did I give him liberty to have any private trade.</p>
               <p>Mr. Massom. I agreed with the prisoner for three pound per month; there was no allowance for any private trade.</p>
